 What Where Find Jobs Advanced Job Search Surface Lab Scientist Micron Technology 1,047 reviews Boise, ID 83716 Micron Technology 1,047 reviews Read what people are saying about working here. Our vision is to transform how the world uses information to enrich life.  Join an inclusive team passionate about one thing: using their expertise in the relentless pursuit of innovation for customers and partners. The solutions we build help make everything from virtual reality experiences to breakthroughs in neural networks possible. We do it all while committing to integrity, sustainability, and giving back to our communities. Because doing so can fuel the very innovation we are pursuing. 
Surface lab scientists are expected to utilize state-of-the-art surface analysis metrologies to support developmental and high-volume manufacturing activities worldwide. Additionally, the laboratory is involved with research innovations designed to improve metrology capability within the Micron community at the highest possible level. 
Technique ownership 
Use of good judgment, initiative, flexibility, and problem-solving skills to provide solutions for both routine and non-routine situations. 
Continuous improvement 
Develop, implement, and utilize new surface analysis strategies and procedures to support development and production of next generation memory solutions. Enable ground-breaking technologies and novel semiconductor manufacturing by investigating material properties in partnership with Micron Engineers and scientists. 
Research, gather, and analyze information related to specific assignments within your technical discipline. Recommend process or equipment changes to improve lab metrics. 
Interpret results of new or modified equipment or processes and determine how they may impact our laboratory or production capability or capacity. 
Support manufacturing requests 
Our team supports manufacturing and R&D requests using a variety of analytical metrologies. Experience with techniques including D-SIMS, RBS, and Mercury Probe is highly preferred. 
Interaction and Communication 
The ability to sustain clear lines of communication allowing for a quick response to team member analytical questions is required. Expectations include interacting positively within the laboratory and other organizations both within and external to Micron. The nature of Micron's organization requires constant and consistent communication regarding projects, procedures, troubleshooting methods, etc. Presenting results in a clear and concise manner through oral presentations, analytical reports, and technical papers is a significant responsibility. 
General Expectations 
Demonstrate proficient knowledge of data collection and analytical strategies and techniques to contribute to group objectives. 
Actively contribute to the fulfillment of all group objectives. 
Execute projects within guidelines defined by management. 
Regularly review data with a high level of detail. 
Demonstrate sound data analysis and judgment when performing and reporting on analyses. 
Present reports and findings with appropriate conclusions and recommendations based upon the results. 
Successful candidates for this position will have: 
Knowledge of structural and chemical surface analysis techniques through coursework or experience. The use of D-SIMS, RBS, and Mercury Probe to explore material properties is preferred. 
Knowledge of and experience with computer programming, Matlab and Visual Basic experience highly desired. 
Have excellent interpersonal skills and demonstrate the ability to thrive in both an individual and team-based work environment. 
Be proactive and take ownership of assigned projects. 
An aptitude and interest in instrument repair and maintenance. 
Excellent computer application skills, particularly with Microsoft Office and instrument control software. 
An ability to work in a flexible manner that allows for changes in assignments and priorities depending upon the identified needs of the laboratory. 
Micron Benefits 
Employee Rewards Program, Healthcare, Paid time off (Combined Sick and Vacation Time), Retirement savings plans, Paid maternity/paternity leave, Employee Assistance Program, Professional development training, Workplace wellness programs, Micron Health Clinic (Boise only), Fitness Center / Activity rooms (Boise only), Tuition Reimbursement, Micron Corporate Discounts, Casual Dress attire. 
About Micron Technology, Inc. 
We are an industry leader in innovative memory and storage solutions. Through our global brands – Micron® and Crucial® – our broad portfolio of high-performance memory and storage technologies, including DRAM, NAND, 3D XPoint™ memory and NOR, is transforming how the world uses information to enrich life. Backed by more than 40 years of technology leadership, our memory and storage solutions enable disruptive trends, including artificial intelligence, 5G, machine learning and autonomous vehicles, in key market segments like mobile, data center, client, consumer, industrial, graphics, automotive, and networking. Our common stock is traded on the Nasdaq under the MU symbol. To learn more visit micron.com/careers. 
 
All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, national origin, veteran or disability status. 
 
